title: Alex Munive’s CV
text:
Economics Student | Data & Research Specialist

alexmunviec@gmail.com | linkedin.com/in/alexm-munive



Student Support Data & Research Specialist at BYU-Idaho


Data analysis, research design, institutional assessment, and student success strategies



Higher education analytics, human capital development, economic behavior, and public policy impact




Dec 2025
Brigham Young University – Idaho, Rexburg, ID
Bachelor of Science in Economics
- Minor: Data Science
- GPA: 3.7
- Relevant Courses: Social Media Marketing, Professional Presentations, Business Writing, Human Resources, Microeconomics, Statistics, Macroeconomics
Dec 2023
Brigham Young University – Idaho, Rexburg, ID
Human Resources Management Certificate



Jan 2023 – Present
Student Support, BYU-Idaho, Rexburg, ID
Data & Research Specialist
- Implemented statistical analyses to develop support programs and data-driven strategies that reduced the percentage of struggling students
- Created Power BI visual reports to communicate complex statistical information to stakeholders
Apr 2023 – Dec 2023
Institutional Research & Assessment, BYU-Idaho, Rexburg, ID
Research & Assessment Specialist
- Led focus groups for executive offices, gathering insights into student experiences
- Presented research findings via reports, presentations, and meetings
- Conducted evaluations of programs and initiatives based on trends and outcomes
Jan 2022 – Jul 2023
Career and Academic Advising, BYU-Idaho, Rexburg, ID
Peer Advisor Team Lead
- Organized and led weekly training meetings for 15+ advisors
- Worked with leadership and department chairs on strategic and curriculum decisions
- Supported students facing academic challenges by developing recovery pathways
Feb 2021 – Aug 2021
Scotiabank, Mexico City, MX
Customer Care Advisor
- Assisted 250+ account holders with financial guidance
- Resolved escalated customer concerns with empathy and professionalism
- Adhered to privacy and security policies while handling sensitive data



Sep 2017 – Jan 2019
Mexican Red Cross, Mexico City, Mexico
Emergency Medical Technician - B
- Responded to emergency calls and administered immediate medical care
- Managed dispatch operations and resource allocation
- Delivered life-saving interventions under pressure
